need to be able to make a great crÃ¨me, crÃ¨me

00:44:28.789 --> 00:44:32.971
brulee in order to judge a great crÃ¨me brulee.
And what's really interesting is, for some

00:44:32.971 --> 00:44:36.690
reason, it often gets hashed out, not just
in regard to me, but in general cause most,

00:44:36.690 --> 00:44:42.710
most restaurant critics aren't extraordinary
accomplished cooks. Most of them do, probably

00:44:42.710 --> 00:44:49.030
cook more than I ever did or do, but there's
this discussion of like if you haven't worked

00:44:49.030 --> 00:44:53.430
in a restaurant or if you haven't gone to
a culinary academy, do you have any right

00:44:53.430 --> 00:44:57.819
reviewing restaurants? Well, I don't know
of many movie critics who've been to film

00:44:57.819 --> 00:45:02.619
school or ever stepped behind a camera or
even been on a film set. I don't know of any,

00:45:02.619 --> 00:45:06.670
most book critics haven't written books and
that's not such a kind of rarified thing to

00:45:06.670 --> 00:45:12.140
do. I think that to be a critic of whatever
you're criticizing, the one thing you need

00:45:12.140 --> 00:45:17.520
is to have really, really exposed yourself
to the broadest possible world of experience

00:45:17.520 --> 00:45:22.660
in that thing. You need to know, you need
to know what greatness is when you see it

00:45:22.660 --> 00:45:27.220
and you need to know when something falls
short and the best way to know that is to

00:45:27.220 --> 00:45:32.569
have had such a wealth of experiences; to
have a kind of yardstick that is so much more

00:45:32.569 --> 00:45:38.380
finely calibrated and so much longer than
other peoples, that when you say this is the

00:45:38.380 --> 00:45:43.040
best short rib entre in the city, you know
what you're talking about because you've tried

00:45:43.040 --> 00:45:46.960
almost all of them. I don't think you need
to be able to go home and make it. And I think

00:45:46.960 --> 00:45:53.140
you can also, I mean, I find when I do, when
I do take stabs at cooking, I mean I'm exaggerating

00:45:53.140 --> 00:45:57.740
my incompetence, but I can look at a recipe
in a cookbook and I can make little tweaks

00:45:57.740 --> 00:46:02.410
and end up liking it a lot better because
I do know a lot about how flavors work together

00:46:02.410 --> 00:46:06.471
and I do know like, what's going to be an
engine of moistness and what's gonna be the

00:46:06.471 --> 00:46:12.800
opposite. I just don't, I'm just an impatient
person when it comes to the time and, and

00:46:12.800 --> 00:46:17.670
patience necessary to kind of put together
a great meal. It usually ends up watching

00:46:17.670 --> 00:46:18.670
something I DVR'd instead on the TV or something.

00:46:18.670 --> 00:46:19.670
&gt;&gt;audience member #9: Great. And then my second
question is, in terms of kind of a celebrity

00:46:19.670 --> 00:46:20.670
chef movement and the new attention that we're
getting with Top Chef and all these shows,

00:46:20.670 --> 00:46:25.480
do you think that that's a positive influence
on the restaurant or culinary world or is

00:46:25.480 --> 00:46:34.960
it detracting from the genuine nature of it?

00:46:34.960 --> 00:46:41.200
&gt;&gt;Frank: I think it's both. I think that one,
on the po-, in, in a positive sense what Top

00:46:41.200 --> 00:46:47.799
Chef and a lot of those shows have done is
they've, they've gotten more people interested

00:46:47.799 --> 00:46:53.859
in food and in restaurants than formerly were.
And that's a kind of market that then exists

00:46:53.859 --> 00:47:01.190
that allows a lot more chefs to take economic
risks, to open places, to, to try things out

00:47:01.190 --> 00:47:06.150
because they've got a more willing and rapt
audience than they've ever had before so that's

00:47:06.150 --> 00:47:11.990
really, really positive. I think on the negative
side, the, the kind of commercialization of

00:47:11.990 --> 00:47:19.369
food entertainment has sent a message to a
lot of young chefs to be that they are, that

00:47:19.369 --> 00:47:23.970
what they're after and what this world promises
them is fame and riches and, and they're faces

00:47:23.970 --> 00:47:28.590
on billboards. And that actually is only gonna
happen for a very few people and so, I think

00:47:28.590 --> 00:47:34.030
the, the danger and the negative part is that
some of the wrong people will be attracted

00:47:34.030 --> 00:47:40.500
for the wrong reasons to the hard, hard, hard
work, of-of-of cooking in a restaurant because

00:47:40.500 --> 00:47:47.430
